 MBOMBELA – A passenger has died when BMW hit  a tree along the R40 this morning. ER24 together with the provincial emergency services responded to a report of a single-vehicle accident around 09:00. According to information from ER24, the car was traveling from the White River direction towards Mbombela, when it lost control between the Bosch Street and R40 island. ALSO READ: Fire brigade understaffed and underequipped  The car with five occupants went off the road then collided with a tree. Two passengers sustained minor injuries and two were seriously injured. The jaws of life had to be used to get the four occupants out of the car. The injured occupants were taken to Rob Ferreira Hospital. ALSO READ: Don’t act like you’re in the dark about LEDs 